					<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/index.php/Gamification:Main" title="Gamification:Main"> Gamification Page</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://blog.softwareinsider.org/2011/01/20/trends-5-engagement-factors-for-gamification-and-the-enterprise/">Five levers of engagement</a> Useful in designing the core elements of any game, by Ray Wang</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.4squarebadges.com/foursquare-badge-list/">Foursquare's Badge Encyclopedia</a> Gives a nice overview of foursquare's iconic approach to badges, from the practical to the zany</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://urban360.me/?goback=%2Egde_3731828_member_152105361">URBAN 360º</a> How the addition of urban game-like programs, crowd sourced initiatives in real/digital spaces and temporary urbanism can improve the life in smart and connected cities</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gamification">Wikipedia</a> Gamification by definition of Wikipedia</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://gamification-research.org">Gamification Research Network</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://gamesandimpact.org/national-conversation-on-games">National Conversation on Games</a> Brief white papers highlighting the opportunities, challenges and best practices for harnessing the power of computer and video games to help address social, cultural, scientific and economic challenges.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://gamification.org/">Gamification.org</a> a gamification wiki - Great resources on our topic of choice!</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.dreig.eu/caparazon/2010/02/28/jessie-schell-y-la-vida-como-un-juego-autenticidad-artificial/">Spanish abstract about Jesse Schell video</a> Artículo resumen de la charla de Jesse Schell y la vida como un juego: Autenticidad artificial</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.diigo.com/list/bowdenartist/gamification">Karen's List of Gamification Links</a> You can subscribe via RSS to my list on Diigo to receive an update each time I add new items.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://mediaevolution.se/en/projekt/our-first-publication-of-the-year-gamification">Gamification by Media Evolution</a> How we can use game mechanics in areas that are not a game - a pocket guide.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.gartner.com/technology/research/gamification/">Gartner's Gamification page</a> Gartner, a leading research and consulting firm, followed by IT, puts gamifaction in a business context and shares some free research and opinions.</li>
</ul>

